<plot>The 2003 version of the annual Bodil awards show saw actress 'Paprika Steen' (qv) and film _Elsker dig for evigt (2002)_ (qv) attracting primary attention. Show-wise, the two-hour televised presentation included an interview-based pre-show, an introductory speech by 'Kim Skotte' (qv), filmed sketches by hosts 'Pernille Højmark' (qv) and 'Søren Østergaard' (qv), a trip down memory lane with late actress 'Bodil Kjer' (qv) and the presentation of a total of ten statuettes, including three special prizes to screenwriters 'Mogens Rukov' (qv), 'Kim Fupz Aakeson' (qv) and 'Anders Thomas Jensen' (qv). Following the televised part, the evening continued with dinner and a movie, the gala premiere of _Grønne slagtere, De (2003)_ (qv).</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?077579</url></doc>
